                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/964: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="from"
                        >Grew</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-27T14:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 27, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 27—3:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. A press ban has been issued here forbidding comment on the “current
                    negotiations between the government of “Manchukuo” and the administration of
                    North China.”</p>
                <p>The Embassy has no further information concerning the matter.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
